race.comment: NEPELA (3) was in the money two starts back at Wodonga but couldn't back it up last time when seventh, beaten 3.5 lengths, at Wagga over 1200m. Finds a tougher race but a big run will not surprise. SOO KISS ME (12) progressed nicely last time out to finish just a long neck from the winner in second over 1200m at Hay. This looks a good race for her and she is one of the key runners. MISS LOTTIE (9) has been beaten similar margins at her two runs back from a spell but will be fitter for them and interestingly drops back to a distance that she performs well at. DENSETSU (8) missed the placings two runs back then didn't feature last start when 3.5 lengths away in seventh over 1000m at Wagga. Taking on a better line-up this time but he is good enough to play a major role. BROMEO (10) missed the placings two runs back then didn't feature last start when 9 lengths away in 14th over 1200m at Swan Hill. Finds a nice race and can play a significant role.
